saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/07140850\/evora-portugal-Praca-do-Giraldo-600x750.jpg 600w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/07140850\/evora-portugal-Praca-do-Giraldo-24x30.jpg\" src=\"\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/07140850\/evora-portugal-Praca-do-Giraldo.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"h-5-the-chapel-of-bones-church-of-st-francis\">5. The Chapel of Bones (Church of St Francis)<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Church of St Francis is famous for the Capela dos Ossos (The Chapel of Bones). The ossuary displays the bones of over 5,000 bodies discovered in the graveyards of the city. It was created by Franciscan monks who wanted to show people that we all meet the same fate, regardless of status. Don&#x2019;t forget to look out for the inscription carved above the entrance that reads &#x2018;we bones that are here, await yours&#x2019;.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--attractions \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--attractions\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong data-rich-text-format-boundary=\"true\">Entrance Fee: <\/strong>Entrance to the church is free. To visit The Chapel of Bones it&#x2019;s 2 EUR<\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones.jpg\" alt=\"evora chapel of bones\"><\/noscript><img width=\"441\" height=\"338\" alt=\"evora chapel of bones\" class=\"wp-image-56728 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones.jpg 1920w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones-783x600.jpg 783w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones-1057x810.jpg 1057w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones-441x338.jpg 441w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones-30x23.jpg 30w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones-163x125.jpg 163w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones-235x180.jpg 235w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones-768x588.jpg 768w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones-1024x785.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones-1410x1080.jpg 1410w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones-1880x1440.jpg 1880w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones-300x230.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones-600x460.jpg 600w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones-30x23.jpg\" src=\"\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/27085053\/evora-chapel-of-bones.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Tip:<\/strong> Interested to discover more history in Evora? Next to the church are some beautiful public gardens, where you can find the ruins of the old palace.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/07192127\/portugal-house.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/noscript><img width=\"261\" height=\"338\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-55309 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1483px) 100vw, 1483px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/07192127\/portugal-house.jpg 1483w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/07192127\/portugal-house-463x600.jpg 463w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/07192127\/portugal-house-626x810.jpg 626w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/07192127\/portugal-house-261x338.jpg 261w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/07192127\/portugal-house-23x30.jpg 23w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/07192127\/portugal-house-126x163.jpg 126w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/07192127\/portugal-house-139x180.jpg 139w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/07192127\/portugal-house-593x768.jpg 593w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/07192127\/portugal-house-791x1024.jpg